[src:deck-ship/abaft-p01] The body of law that deals with maritime cases.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p01] The Admiralty Court is now in the Rolls Building.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p01] When referring to a vessel, it implies that the vessel is not being or able to be controlled and therefore goes where the wind and current take her; a vessel in this condition may also be described as "loose from her moorings" or "out of place".
