[src:deck-ship/abaft-p01] Any person or thing that is misplaced or missing.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p01] When applied to a member of the Navy or Marine Corps, such a person is said to be "absent without leave" (AWOL) or, in US Navy and US Marine Corps terminology, is guilty of an "unauthorized absence" (UA).
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p01] The term may also be used more generally of any floating object or person.
