[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] The point of origin of net hydrodynamic resistance on the submerged structure of a boat, especially a sailboat.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] will align vertically with the center of lateral resistance.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] serves the same purpose but slides vertically rather than pivoting.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] An imaginary line down the center of a vessel lengthwise.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] Any structure or anything mounted or carried on a vessel that straddles this line and is equidistant from either side of the vessel is said to be "on the centerline".
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] Wear on a line or sail caused by constant rubbing against another surface.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] Those equipped with sails have a single mast.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] used by the Basques in the mid-16th century in what is now Newfoundland and Labrador.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] The impatient excitement in a ship's crew as the end of a voyage becomes imminent.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] Characteristics include crew members working harder to get the ship sailing faster, off-watch personnel being on deck to keep track of progress, and everyone being packed and in their shore-going clothes (ready to be paid off) the moment the vessel arrives in port.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] (obsolete usage) A crew member avoiding duties with a feigned illness, usually after leaving port.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] , a trade over which the company held a strict monopoly.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] , though the company usually hired charter ships on special terms and for much shorter periods.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] A compartment from which the ship was navigated, especially in the Royal Navy.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] displayed on a monitor, thereby replacing all manual navigation functions.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] Chartplotters also display information collected from all shipboard electronic instruments and often directly control autopilots.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p03] pointing forward or aft, often of longer range than other guns.
