[src:deck-ship/abaft-p04] A light illuminating a sector or very narrow angle and intended to mark a direction to be followed.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p04] A vessel ranging in size from a small boat to a large ship tasked to carry military dispatches from ship to ship, from ship to shore, or, occasionally, from shore to shore.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p04] The weight of water displaced by the immersed volume of a ship's hull, exactly equivalent to the weight of the whole ship.
