[src:deck-ship/abaft-p07] The lead ship is usually, but not always, the first of her class to be completed and often, but not always, the class as a whole is known by her name.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p07] To do his job, a sailor must be able to identify each rope from all the many options – and in the dark.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p07] the wrong one may not only be inefficient but also potentially dangerous.
