[src:deck-ship/abaft-p07] The side of a ship that is sheltered from the wind; i.e. the side that is downwind, or in the direction toward which the wind is blowing.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p07] A large fan-shaped wooden board or fin mounted in pairs on the side of a boat.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p07] in nautical use) In the direction toward which the wind is blowing.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p07] of a vessel before encountering hazards.
[src:deck-ship/abaft-p07] The measure generally allows for a reasonable estimate of the vessel's carrying capacity, as it excludes the small, often unusable volume contained in her overhanging ends.
